obo:ECO_0007719  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_5310  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Extensive immunoelectron microscopy Cav2.1 (CACNA1A) was performed. Knockout mice were used to validate specificity.\n\n\"Postsynaptically, virtually all PC spines were immunoreactive for the α1A protein. Peroxidase reaction end-product for the channel subunit accumulated in dendritic spines postsynaptic to PF (Fig. 2C) and CF (Fig. 2D) varicosities.\"\n\n\"At the electron microscopic level, the most intense immunoreactivity for the α1A subunit was found in the presynaptic active zone of parallel fibre varicosities. The dendritic spines of Purkinje cells were also strongly labelled with the highest density of immunoparticles detected within 180 nm from the edge of the asymmetrical parallel fibre-Purkinje cell synapses.\"\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Immunocytochemistry for electron microscopy\nAdult male rats (n = 9), P14 wild-type and α1A-deficient mice (n = 2) were perfused with the same solutions as described for light microscopy.\"\n\nantibody:\n\"A polyclonal antibody specific for the α1A subunit of P/Q-type calcium channel was produced by Alomone Laboratories (Jerusalem, Israel). Briefly, the antibody was raised in rabbits against a synthetic peptide corresponding to an intracellular loop between domains II and III (amino acid residues 865-881/CNA1/) of the α1A subunit (Mori et al., 1991; Starr et al., 1991) and then affinity purified on immobilized CNA1. \"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5310" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

